    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "Presenting a mechanically sorted 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine. This example features a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a reinforced rear main seal, ensuring long-term reliability of the internal rotating assembly. The G96 six-speed manual gearbox provides crisp engagement, paired with a chassis that benefits from refreshed control arm bushings and Bilstein B6 dampers. While the exterior shows honest road-going patina consistent with a well-loved driver, the engine retains excellent thermal management and a linear power delivery up to the 7,200 RPM redline. A superb entry point for the purist seeking the communicative hydraulic steering and rear-engine dynamics of the analog 911 era.",
